	,"x4freetext":[" The angles and energies of light-ion ejectiles"
		,"were measured using the Silicon Detector Array SIDAR"
		,"covering laboratory angles between 138deg and 165deg."
		,"Oak Ridge Rutgers University Barrel Array ORRUBA"
		,"covered laboratory angles between 45deg and 135deg."
		,"The ORRUBA position-sensitive silicon strip detectors"
		,"with thickness of 1000 mu-m were mounted at a radius"
		,"of 76 mm at laboratory angles forward of 95deg and at"
		,"a radius of 87 mm at more backward angles. An angular"
		,"resolution of better than 2deg in polar angle was"
		,"achieved."]
